text: Buckinghamshire (abbreviated Bucks) is a county in central England, near the south and London. The county town is named Aylesbury. == Cities, towns and villages == Locations marked with a (*) are a part of the cerimonal county of Buckinghamshire, but are governed by the Borough of Milton Keynes. * Amersham * Aylesbury * Beaconsfield * Bletchley* * Buckingham * Chesham * Eton* * Fenny Stratford* * High Wycombe * Marlow * Milton Keynes* * Newport Pagnell* * Olney* * Princes Risborough * Slough* * Stony Stratford* * Wendover * Winslow * Wolverton* Category:Ceremonial counties of England
